{
  "texts": [
    "Fleiss' kappa values show only a slight agreement between Radboud and Mayo (κ = 0.055), and a fair agreement between Radboud and Münster (κ = 0.295) as well as Mayo and Münster (κ = 0.254).",
    "These results suggest that the lower scores assigned by Radboud pathologists may be influenced, at least in part, by subjective differences in interpretation rather than solely reflecting deficiencies in the AI-generated reports.",
    "The disagreement between pathologists highlights how inter-observer variability can influence study results and suggests that the perceived accuracy of HistoGPT reports may vary depending on the individual or institution performing the evaluation.",
    "The three clinical evaluations confirm our previous findings that His-toGPT performs well for common diseases, but worse for rare diseases (Figs. 3a, e, 4d, e, and 6c).",
    "Thus, as with all machine learning algorithms, its quality is limited by its training data 44 -in our case, the Munich cohort."
  ]
}